 <p>
  A version of this sign is: ASSERTIVE:
  <br/>
  Assertive uses the same movement as "emotion" but has "A" handshapes instead 
  of "E" handshapes.
  <br/>
  The movement is circular --up, out, down, back.  Note: if you do the 
  movement the opposite way, down, out, up, back--it means "act" (as in 
	"actor).
  <br/>
  <img border="0" height="214" src="/images/theate1.jpg" width="233"/>
  <br/>
  If you do the sign ASSERTIVE a little faster and with a more "angry" facial 
  expression it means "aggressive."
 </p>
